OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWomen to get gay-conviction
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpardons for first time     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Women convicted of offences related to 
OL,6, being gay can apply to have their      
OL,7, convictions removed, under an expansion
OL,8, of the government's pardon scheme.     
OL,10,FThe Disregards and Pardons Scheme,     
OL,11,Flaunched in England an Wales in 2012,  
OL,12,Finitially applied to only men - and    
OL,13,Fspecified offences.                    
OL,15,FNow, anyone convicted or cautioned     
OL,16,Funder former laws related to same-sex  
OL,17,Factivity can apply.                    
OL,19,FOne charity welcomed the move but said 
OL,20,Fpardons should be automatic.           
